The paper focuses on learning a better representation with neural networks, which is a common problem in machine learning and falls under the category of "Learning" (cs.LG). The paper specifically mentions evaluating the approach on two types of models, Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs) and Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs), which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) tasks. The paper also mentions introducing novel loss components to improve clustering, which falls under the category of "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI). Finally, the paper mentions that the proposed approach does not require a complicated training procedure, which suggests that it may also fall under the category of "Neural and Evolutionary Computing" (cs.NE).
